  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "A significant data security challenge in blockchain technology is the risk of 51% attacks.",
    "In a blockchain network, a 51% attack occurs when a single entity or group controls over 50% of the network's computing power, enabling them to manipulate the network and potentially steal sensitive data.",
    "Although rare, such attacks pose a substantial risk to the security of blockchain networks (Nakamoto 2008).",
    "Smart contracts also introduce data security concerns due to potential vulnerabilities.",
    "Since smart contracts contain sensitive information and execute automatically, vulnerabilities within them can be exploited, potentially leading to the compromise of sensitive data."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Although rare, such attacks pose a substantial risk to the security of blockchain networks (Nakamoto 2008)."
  ]
}